                  <nationality type="Ethiopia"/>
                  <faith type="EOTC"/>
                  
                  
                  <occupation type="literary">writer</occupation>
              
               <birth when="1928">He was born at <placeName ref="LOC3786Harar"/> in<date>1928</date>. </birth>
                  
                  
                  
                  <floruit notBefore="1953" notAfter="1988">He was the prominent Ethiopian author, poet and playwright. At his childhood,
                     he received a traditional church education and modern education in the elementary school opened by the Italians for natives. 
                     After liberation, he continued his modern education at a government school. Then, he joined Kotabe Secondary School. He completed his graduate studies in 
                     <placeName ref="Q145"/> and he returned to <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop"/> in <date>1953/54</date>.
                     He served at Civil Aviation, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Ministry of Culture and later transfered to <placeName ref="LOC1216AddisA"/>
                     University to teach at the Department of Theatre Arts.
                     
                  </floruit>
               <death when="1988">He died at <placeName ref="LOC1216AddisA"/> in <date>1988</date>.</death>
                  
                  
